                    "company": "ATG Europe",
                    "description": "\ud835\udc0c\ud835\udc13\ud835\udc06-\ud835\udc08, \ud835\udc05\ud835\udc25\ud835\udc1e\ud835\udc31\ud835\udc22\ud835\udc1b\ud835\udc25\ud835\udc1e \ud835\udc02\ud835\udc28\ud835\udc26\ud835\udc1b\ud835\udc22\ud835\udc27\ud835\udc1e\ud835\udc1d \ud835\udc08\ud835\udc26\ud835\udc1a\ud835\udc20\ud835\udc1e\ud835\udc2b (\ud835\udc05\ud835\udc02\ud835\udc08):\n\u2022 Act as the ESA technical interface for the FCI instrument liaising with industry and Partner Agency (EUMETSAT) and internally with the MTG teams.\n\u2022 Responsible to follow the progress on the assembly, integration and testing of the flight models at subsystem and instrument level.\n\u2022 Provided technical support to the on-ground instrument performance characterization and verification. Including the review of test requirement specifications and evaluation of system level performance resulting from the test measurement results.\n\u2022 Install, maintain and operate for internal purposes instrument\u2019s performance models delivered by industry.\n\u2022 Was key in the evaluation of the instruments optical performance using appropriate tools and\ntechniques in order to identify and quantify any variances and corrective actions as needed.\n\u2022 Proposed corrective actions to resolve instrument hardware and performance issues.\n\u2022 Provided expert support to reviews, such as instrument critical design review, subsystem and instrument test results review, non-compliance reviews, qualification reviews.\n\u2022 Recurrent reporting to payload product manager.\n\n\ud835\udc12\ud835\udc1e\ud835\udc27\ud835\udc2d\ud835\udc22\ud835\udc27\ud835\udc1e\ud835\udc25-\ud835\udfd0\ud835\udc02 & \ud835\udc03, \ud835\udc0c\ud835\udc2e\ud835\udc25\ud835\udc2d\ud835\udc22-\ud835\udc12\ud835\udc29\ud835\udc1e\ud835\udc1c\ud835\udc2d\ud835\udc2b\ud835\udc1a\ud835\udc25 \ud835\udc08\ud835\udc27\ud835\udc2c\ud835\udc2d\ud835\udc2b\ud835\udc2e\ud835\udc26\ud835\udc1e\ud835\udc27\ud835\ud